The retail price of petrol in South Africa will decrease by more than 5% from July 5, while the price of wholesale diesel will fall by nearly 5.2%, the energy department said on Saturday. The price of petrol will fall by 69 cents to R12.86 a litre in the commercial hub of Gauteng province, while diesel will go down by 60 cents to R10.97 a litre, the department said in a statement.